// Typical FAANG batch pipeline (conceptual)
// 1. Airflow triggers DAG at 2:00 AM daily
// 2. Spark job reads raw events from S3 (last 24h, ~500GB)
// 3. Spark transforms: filter, join with dimension tables, aggregate
// 4. Write results to BigQuery partitioned table
// 5. Airflow runs data quality checks
// 6. On failure: alert, backfill strategy triggered
// 7. On success: downstream dashboards and ML pipelines update

// SAP-to-FAANG data concept mapping
// SAP ECC Table          -> Kafka Topic (event stream)
// SAP BW InfoCube        -> BigQuery table (analytical)
// ABAP Report            -> Spark job + Looker dashboard
// BW Process Chain       -> Airflow DAG
// DataSource/Extraction  -> Data contract + schema registry
// Transport Request      -> CI/CD pipeline with schema validation
// InfoObject             -> Column with data type and constraints
// ODS/DSO                -> Data lake raw zone (bronze layer)
